Package: AccumulatR
Type: Package
Title: Simulation and Likelihood Tools for Evidence-Accumulation Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Niek", "Stevenson", email = "niek.stevenson@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
  )
Description: Toolbox for designing, simulating and fitting custom evidence-accumulation
    models to behavioral data. Users define a model in terms of accumulators, pooled
    channels, logical response rules, and timing dependencies. This allows more direct
    embedding of psychological hypotheses into the model. With that model you can
    simulate decision-making data and evaluate the likelihood of observed responses 
    under alternative parameter values. The user-facing interface stays in R, while the
    likelihood calculations are handled in C++ for speed.
